# Shared Types

- All TypeScript interfaces and types used by both the Angular client and the Node.js server must live in the `shared/` directory.
- Never duplicate type definitions across client and server.
- Shared types include: WebSocket message payloads, character stats, item definitions, skill definitions, game constants.
- Import shared types using a path alias (e.g., `@shared/`) in both client and server.
